Flag SVG provenance and license
================================

Source: flag-icons (https://github.com/lipis/flag-icons), the 4x3 aspect-ratio
SVG set, commit fetched 2026-07-15 from the `main` branch.

License: MIT (Copyright (c) 2013 Panayiotis Lipiridis). Full text below.

These files were copied individually into this directory (no npm dependency,
no CDN reference, no runtime fetch - design-system.md flag-SVG exception).
Each file is named by its ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code:

cn.svg de.svg es.svg fr.svg gb.svg id.svg in.svg it.svg
jp.svg kr.svg pt.svg ru.svg sa.svg th.svg vn.svg

Flags represent COUNTRIES, chosen as a defensible per-language mapping (see
src/lib/languages.ts) - the language name is always the primary label, the
flag a secondary decorative visual (never flag-only), per design-system.md
and frontend.md.

